## Why Does Melancholic Writing Feel Beautiful?
Why do humans enjoy sad poetry, tragic novels, heartbreak
songs, lonely aesthetics?

Humans do not read literature for happiness.
They want to be understood, seen, and to process emotions.
Melancholic writing transforms pain into meaning.

When literature perfectly describes grief and emptiness,
readers feel: someone understood what I could not explain.

Melancholic writing contains memory, loss, time and longing.
Writers believed intense emotions reveal truth.

Literature gives language to emotions people struggle 
to carry alone.

Melancholic writing taught people to suppress emotions,
control themselves while transforming pain, emotions,
tragic endings and longings into art.

## The Symbolism of Seasons in Literature
Before psychology had words for human emotions,
nature had metaphors.

Spring — new beginnings after suffering.
Summer — peak of life, youth, everything having its moment.
Autumn — letting go of things not meant for you.
Winter — loss, grief, silence.

Human emotions are messy, joyful, hopeful and sad.
When a writer suffers, they often use seasons to represent
their sorrow.

Autumn was my favourite yet winter became my heart
when I was deeply craving for spring and summer.
